    "The high temporal resolution comes from the climate and GPP product data, which provide daily information on environmental conditions and ecosystem carbon inputs.",
    "The procedures for generating highresolution predictions across the U.S. Midwest are given in the \"Methods\" section.",
    "The multi-year-averaged SLOPE GPP data and the carbon fluxes generated by KGML-ag-Carbon are closer to the EC flux tower observations (same dataset used in Fig. 2) than estimates from Trendy 35, a widely used carbon flux ensemble product generated by a suite of dynamic global vegetation models (Fig.",
    "Although methods for evaluating KGML-ag-Carbon are somewhat limited at the regional scale, EC flux tower data and Trendy are suitable datasets for comparison in the absence of ideal benchmarks for this large region.",
